Conservative leader <a0_0><b7_0>Nicolas Sarkozy<b7_0/><a0_0/> got his best score in Alsace (<b3_0>over 65%<b3_0/>) in the second round of the French presidential elections of 2007. The frequently changing status of the région throughout history has left its mark on modern day politics in terms of a particular interest in national identity issues. <b5_0>Alsace<b5_0/> is also one of the most pro-<b6_0>EU<b6_0/> regions of France.
